Hello,

I'm using nRF51822-EK board for tests. I'm trying to implement button debouncing and I encountered a problem when trying to use InterruptIn and Tickers with last version of mbed-src.
Here is example code:

``` C
#include "mbed.h"

DigitalOut led1(LED1);
DigitalOut led2(LED2);

InterruptIn button(BUTTON1);
Ticker ticker_button_debounce;

void periodicCallback1(void)
{
}

void button_debounce(void)
{
    led2 = !led2;
    ticker_button_debounce.detach();
}

void button_hit_interrupt (void)
{
    led1 = !led1;
    ticker_button_debounce.attach(button_debounce, 0.001);
}

int main()
{
    led1 = 0;
    led2 = 0;

    Ticker ticker_led1;
    ticker_led1.attach(periodicCallback1, 1);

    button.mode(PullUp);
    wait(.001);
    button.fall(&button_hit_interrupt);

    while(1);
}
```

When I push the button it should turn on/off LED1 and LED2 with 1ms delay between them.
What I get:
1. Device powered on, all leds is off.
2. Push the button one time for a short time.
3. LED1 will immediately turn on.
4. LED2 will turn on after a few hundreds of milliseconds (it vary).
5. Push the button second time.
6. LED1 will turn off immediately.
7. LED2 doesn't turn off.
8. After this if I push button then LED1 will toggle, but LED2 will stay turned on.
Next if I delete this line from code:

``` C
ticker_led1.attach(periodicCallback1, 1);
```

Then all works fine and button_debounce() callback is called as normal every time.

