After trying (unsuccessfully) for several hours to port a working project to the LPC1549, I've encountered numerous bugs with the serial_api implementation:
- Attaching a TxIrq callback causes the microcontroller to lock up. I've narrowed this down to the following line: `obj->uart->INTENSET = (1 << ((irq == RxIrq) ? 0 : 2))`. As a result, the following program fails to run:

``` c++
#include "mbed.h"

DigitalOut led1(LED1, 1);
Serial pc(USBTX, USBRX);
char buffer[1025];
int idx = 0;

void onTx()
{
    //Send a single byte
    if (idx < sizeof(buffer))
        pc.putc(buffer[idx++]);

    //Toggle the LED
    led1 = !led1;
}

int main()
{
    //Prepare the buffer
    for (int i = 0; i < sizeof(buffer); i++)
        buffer[i] = 'A';

    //Attach the tx interrupt
    pc.attach(onTx, Serial::TxIrq);

    //Start the transfer
    onTx();

    //Don't exit main!
    while (1);
}
```
- Attaching an RxIrq callback appears to work, but the microcontroller locks up when the first character is received. As a result, the following program fails to run:

``` c++
#include "mbed.h"

DigitalOut led1(LED1, 1);
DigitalOut led2(LED2, 1);

Serial pc(USBTX, USBRX);

void onRx()
{
    // Note: you need to actually read from the serial to clear the RX interrupt
    printf("%c\n", pc.getc());
    led2 = !led2;
}

int main()
{
    pc.attach(onRx);

    while (1) {
        led1 = !led1;
        wait(0.5);
    }
}
```
- serial_init() calculates 0x40048000 for LPC_USART2_BASE, but according to LPC15xx.h it is actually located at 0x400C0000. This will prevent USART2 from being used, and will likely cause a crash.

Hi,
Starting [this revision](http://developer.mbed.org/users/mbed_official/code/mbed-src/rev/d73ca02bc818) mbed online compiller creates wrong hex files for nRF51822 projects.
For example if I create new empty project with only main.cpp file:

```
#include "mbed.h"

DigitalOut myled(LED1);

int main() {
    while(1) {
        myled = 1;
        wait(0.2);
        myled = 0;
        wait(0.2);
    }
}
```

And import mbed-src library from [this revision](http://developer.mbed.org/users/mbed_official/code/mbed-src/rev/d73ca02bc818) then after project compiles it'll create wrong hex file with size 4476 bytes and I can't flash it into device with error:
ERROR: Error in opening or parsing mbed_blinky_NRF51822_.hex file.
But if I import mbed-src library from [previous revision](http://developer.mbed.org/users/mbed_official/code/mbed-src/rev/1c135c664c6b) with old softdevice then all works fine: compiler creates hex file with size 244960 bytes and I can flash it into my device without errors.

I compiled blinky example with mbed-tools and checked it on my board and it works fine. So it's online compiler fault.

Here is [this issue reported on mbed.org.](http://developer.mbed.org/users/mbed_official/code/mbed-src/issues/9)

